<div id="review_3836255918" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3836255918" />
    <a title="Luís" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/117399210-lu-s"><img alt="Luís" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1620236159p2/117399210.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3836255918?book_show_action=true">Feb 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Luís" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Luís" href="/user/show/117399210-lu-s">Luís</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789897021824" href="/book/show/29244971-os-lus-adas">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=portugal">portugal</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=poetry">poetry</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=2021-readings">2021-readings</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3836255918" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12191649070796618983">The maritime feat and the Portuguese vocation mythologized on a superhuman level in Modern Literature.<br/>It was writing by the tireless hero, traveller, preacher of freedom. In the middle of the 16th century, they narrate epically part of the history of Portugal, the heroic deeds of the Lusitanians and in particular, the journey of Vasco da Gama in the discovery of the sea path to India in the years 1498/1499 during the reign of D. Manuel I, king of Portugal.<br/>These Poems are divided into ten songs w</span>
  <span id="freeText12191649070796618983" style="display:none">The maritime feat and the Portuguese vocation mythologized on a superhuman level in Modern Literature.<br />It was writing by the tireless hero, traveller, preacher of freedom. In the middle of the 16th century, they narrate epically part of the history of Portugal, the heroic deeds of the Lusitanians and in particular, the journey of Vasco da Gama in the discovery of the sea path to India in the years 1498/1499 during the reign of D. Manuel I, king of Portugal.<br />These Poems are divided into ten songs with 1102 stanzas predominantly octave of heroic and some sapphic decasyllables and were published for the first time in 1572, in Lisbon special edition dedicated to King D. Sebastião to which Camões read it. In the Lusíadas, Camões recovered a literary style already used in Classical Antiquity by Homer in his works: "The Iliad" and "The Odyssey". While he inspired by his imagination to write them, Camões inspired by Vasco da Gama's Journey's adventures and incidences.<br />They also included Roman and Greek mythology elements, examples of Neptune, God of the Seas. Venus, Goddess of Love and protector of the Portuguese in the Council of the Gods in opposition to Jupiter, God of War. Bacchus, God of the Feasts and his son Luso, gave rise to the Portuguese word. Also, some elements of the popular imagination, namely "Velho do Restelo", "O Gigante Adamastor", and "Ninfas do Tejo".<br /><br />See other of my critic reviews of this author:<br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3669531010">https://www.goodreads.com/review/show...</a><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3830454036">https://www.goodreads.com/review/show...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="12191649070796618983" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


