<div id="review_2467945825" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2467945825" />
    <a title="Eva" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/84556572-eva"><img alt="Eva" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1547210975p2/84556572.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2467945825?book_show_action=true">Mar 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eva" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eva" href="/user/show/84556572-eva">Eva</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/84556572-eva?shelf=verse">verse</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2467945825" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1604206199365831235">My experience was a 3/5 but the book itself is a 4/5. Unfortunately, Camões expects you to know the history of Portugal up until the time of writing, a LOT of Roman mythology, as well as other epic tales. He makes many many many references to such things, and if you don&apos;t bother to understand them, his work becomes unbearable to read. <br/><br/>I do highly appraise what he set to achieve. Good epic tales are a rare breed, much less written in goddamn decasyllabic ottava rima, and Portugal sorely lacks pat</span>
  <span id="freeText1604206199365831235" style="display:none">My experience was a 3/5 but the book itself is a 4/5. Unfortunately, Camões expects you to know the history of Portugal up until the time of writing, a LOT of Roman mythology, as well as other epic tales. He makes many many many references to such things, and if you don't bother to understand them, his work becomes unbearable to read. <br /><br />I do highly appraise what he set to achieve. Good epic tales are a rare breed, much less written in goddamn decasyllabic ottava rima, and Portugal sorely lacks patriotism (and afaik, at the time it lacked good written works, Camões did complain about this). Sure, the history told by Vasco da Gama in Melinde was likely not all that accurate, but it sounded dramatic, fantastic, heroic. And certainly much more interesting than whatever I learnt in highschool.<br /><br />Camões' writing in general is pretty good. Everything feels more intense than you'd expect, some verses even flow so well they made my eyes water. And he even managed to make Cupid the most hardcore male god (...partly due to Mars and Jupiter barely having screentime). Pic related: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://pbs.twimg.com/media/D1QQnMvXQAIR-Fu.jpg">pbs.twimg.com/media/D1QQnMvXQAIR-Fu.jpg</a><br /><br />I could do without hearing most of my country's history some 3 times in total or the scene where the gods show the world and the future to Gama. Especially that last part. But I'll blame it on too many references for me to look up. (Also no reference to the Azores? That hurts.)<br /><br />E por amor de deus, arranjem uma versão que use português corrente!! É mesmo só pela ortografia, tipo "commettel-as" VS "cometê-las" porque algumas palavras são simplesmente impossíveis de encontrar no dicionário com a escrita antiga. Ou então é uma palavra perfeitamente comum mas a pessoa não percebe logo porque está tão alterada.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1604206199365831235" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

